			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I keep forgetting this is a thing. Supposedly Sony moved most of their big announcements from their yearly PSX show in December to this instead. I'm not going to do an entire write up like I do with E3, but there were still a few things worth making a thread over.<br />
<br />
For starters, they announced seven or eight new games, but the three that I would say are the biggest deals are Guacamelee 2, Spelunky 2, and Ghost of Tsushima. The first two are sequels to indie darlings that were very highly regarded, the latter is the new game from Sucker Punch. Sucker Punch is probably best known for making the Infamous games. All we really know about Ghost of Tsushima right now is that it is a samurai game and probably takes place during the Mongol Invasion of Japan.<br />
<br />
They also had a bunch of updated trailers for games I didn't expect to hear from again for awhile, including Spider Man, God of War, Detroit Become Human, Monster Hunter, and The Last of Us Part 2. It's probably going to be impossible to not have the nature of this latter trailer spoiled to you, but I want to make it clear that if you are going to attempt a media blackout to start it now. This trailer is fairly significant in ways I will describe in a spoiler tag below. It is not a secret, it is not a spoiler, but whether or not you want to see it now or later is up to you.<br />
